.TH "alloc_iova_fast" 9 "alloc_iova_fast" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
alloc_iova_fast \- allocates an iova from rcache
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned long" alloc_iova_fast
.BI "(struct iova_domain *iovad "  ","
.BI "unsigned long size "  ","
.BI "unsigned long limit_pfn "  ","
.BI "bool flush_rcache "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "iovad" 12
- iova domain in question
.IP "size" 12
- size of page frames to allocate
.IP "limit_pfn" 12
- max limit address
.IP "flush_rcache" 12
- set to flush rcache on regular allocation failure
This function tries to satisfy an iova allocation from the rcache,
and falls back to regular allocation on failure. If regular allocation
fails too and the flush_rcache flag is set then the rcache will be flushed.
